body:
@indrc 

In addition to removing the additional dependency, I think there should be a test for validating the randomness of the chose algorithm, and to make sure there are no conflicts. For a Flink Job with large number of Task Managers and state in Terrabytes resulting in several files, there could be a possibility of conflicts with the current random string generation method. 

fyi @StefanRRichter @StephanEwen

@StephanEwen you're right. there is something could be done to parallelize the creation of input split.
I wonder if the creation of InputSplit is always handled by InputFormat. There have been some ideas, and I will keep working on it.
Thanks for you advice!
